<body>
  <h1>AI Judge Report</h1>
  <p><strong>Baseline exam:</strong> AP CS A (#265)<br/>
     <strong>Variant exam:</strong> AP CS A — Exam variant 2 (#294)<br/>
     <strong>Model:</strong> ollama:gpt-oss:120b<br/>
     <strong>Compared slots:</strong> 47<br/>
     <strong>Review time:</strong> 349.8s</p>

  <h2>Overall score</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Final exam variant score: <strong>85</strong> / 100<br/>
       Base (rubric-only): <strong>98</strong> / 100<br/>
       Usable questions: <strong>100</strong>%<br/>
       Distinctness: <strong>4.02</strong>/5 (factor 0.87)</p>
    <p class="muted">Total score calculation: Final = Base(97.9) × DistinctnessFactor(0.87) × UsabilityFactor(0.99) = 84.9 (clamped to 85/100)</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Instructor summary</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Summary:</strong> The variant closely mirrors the original exam in concept, difficulty, structure, and topic alignment, showing strong overall quality. Minor wording ambiguities and a less distinct framing are the primary areas for improvement.</p>
    <p><strong>Strengths:</strong> High conceptual equivalence, Difficulty level matches well, Clear and solvable structure, Accurate answer key with plausible distractors</p>
    <p><strong>Weaknesses:</strong> Small wording ambiguities in some items, Distractors could be refined for clarity, Variant is only moderately distinct from the baseline</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Aggregate scores</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Conceptual equivalence: <strong>4.96</strong><br/>
       Difficulty similarity: <strong>4.91</strong><br/>
       Structural validity: <strong>4.96</strong><br/>
       Answer correctness: <strong>4.77</strong><br/>
       Topic alignment: <strong>4.98</strong></p>
  </div>

  <h2>Usability</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p>Usable as-is: <strong>44</strong><br/>
       Usable with edits: <strong>3</strong><br/>
       Unusable: <strong>0</strong></p>
  </div>

